  "body": "### Description\n\n**Summary** - Quarkus RESTEasy Reactive should natively support `Uni<RestResponse<Multi<byte[]>>>`\r\n\r\n**Description**\r\n\r\nI am using the solution outlined [here](https://groups.google.com/g/Quarkus-dev/c/odN4RjU_ybE) for streaming binary content using `Multi<byte[]>`.\r\n\r\nIt is essential that the response and headers can be set dynamically. For example `Content-Type` and `ETag`. The latter allows dynamically sending `304 Not Modified` on any later duplicate requests.\r\n\r\nThere has been [discussion](https://quarkusio.zulipchat.com/#narrow/stream/187030-users/topic/Dynamic.20content.20type.20and.20Multi.3Cbyte.5B.5D.20.3E/near/286638048) about this on Zulip.\n\n### Implementation ideas\n\n_No response_",
